<subSubSection box="[151,251,394,420]" pageId="13" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,684,394,1253]" box="[151,251,394,420]" pageId="13" pageNumber="34">REMARKS</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="34" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,684,394,1253]" pageId="13" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Petter" authorityYear="1983" box="[151,306,426,451]" class="Chromadorea" family="Benthimermithidae" genus="Benthimermis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Benthimermithida" pageId="13" pageNumber="34" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="marionensis">
<emphasis box="[151,306,426,451]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="34">B. marionensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described upon eight mature females from the southern part of the Indian Ocean, 
<geoCoordinate box="[248,348,491,517]" degrees="46" direction="south" minutes="52" orientation="latitude" pageId="13" pageNumber="34" precision="925" value="-46.866665">46°52’S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[364,467,491,517]" degrees="37" direction="east" minutes="51" orientation="longitude" pageId="13" pageNumber="34" precision="925" value="37.85">37°51’E</geoCoordinate>
, 
<quantity box="[483,603,490,517]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.05" metricValueMax="11.0" metricValueMin="3.1" pageId="13" pageNumber="34" unit="m" value="70.5" valueMax="110.0" valueMin="31.0">31-110 m</quantity>
depth (
<bibRefCitation author="PETTER A. - J." box="[158,303,523,549]" pageId="13" pageNumber="34" pagination="1 - 15" refId="ref12633" refString="PETTER A. - J. 1983 a. - Quelques nouvelles especes du genre Benthimermis Petter, 1980 (Benthimermithidae: Nematoda) du Sud de l'ocean Indien. Systematic Parasitology 5: 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="1983">Petter 1983a</bibRefCitation>
). The other findings were made in the Southern Atlantic, 
<geoCoordinate box="[413,504,555,581]" degrees="57" direction="south" minutes="09" orientation="latitude" pageId="13" pageNumber="34" precision="925" value="-57.15">57°09’S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[518,620,555,581]" degrees="26" direction="west" minutes="09" orientation="longitude" pageId="13" pageNumber="34" precision="925" value="-26.15">26°09’W</geoCoordinate>
from depth 
<quantity box="[221,306,586,613]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7289999999999999" pageId="13" pageNumber="34" unit="m" value="1729.0">1729 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="TCHESUNOV A. V." box="[320,508,587,613]" pageId="13" pageNumber="34" pagination="12 - 22" refId="ref12846" refString="TCHESUNOV A. V. 1988. - [New finding of deep-sea nematodes of the family Benthimermithidae in the South Atlantic, with description of a new species]. Vestnik Zoologii 6: 12 - 22 (in Russian with English summary)." type="journal article" year="1988">Tchesunov 1988</bibRefCitation>
). The new finding is from absolutely another region and a much greater depth. The new specimen agrees with the original description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Petter" authorityYear="1983" box="[401,555,682,707]" class="Chromadorea" family="Benthimermithidae" genus="Benthimermis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Benthimermithida" pageId="13" pageNumber="34" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="marionensis">
<emphasis box="[401,555,682,707]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="34">B. marionensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in shape of the tail with the terminal spine possessing cytoplasmic core; construction of the gonad and the trophosome. Body length, the de Man “V” index, and the distance from the anterior end to the amphid are in accordance with the original description too (9.0 mm, 53.5%, and 84 µm vs 
<quantity box="[151,320,906,933]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.205" metricValueMax="1.48" metricValueMin="0.93" pageId="13" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="12.05" valueMax="14.8" valueMin="9.3">9.3-14.8 mm</quantity>
, 46.5-74.0%, and 70-85 µm respectively). However the terminal spine of the new specimen is twice shorter than in the original description (130 vs 200-320 µm). Besides, there is no evident anus in the new specimen contrary to 
<typeStatus box="[280,326,1066,1092]" pageId="13" pageNumber="34">type</typeStatus>
specimens (
<bibRefCitation author="PETTER A. - J." box="[460,594,1067,1093]" pageId="13" pageNumber="34" pagination="565 - 578" refId="ref12713" refString="PETTER A. - J. 1987. - Quelques nouvelles especes de femelles du genre Benthimermis Petter, 1980 (Benthimermithidae: Nematoda) des grands fonds de la mer de Norvege. Bulletin du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle 4 e ser., 9, section A (3): 565 - 578." type="journal article" year="1987">Petter 1987</bibRefCitation>
). As the new specimen was found far from the place of the first finding, it is possible that it can belong to another population of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Petter" authorityYear="1983" box="[435,609,1162,1187]" class="Chromadorea" family="Benthimermithidae" genus="Benthimermis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Benthimermithida" pageId="13" pageNumber="34" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="marionensis">
<emphasis box="[435,609,1162,1187]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="34">B. marionensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This suggestion can explain the size differences in several morphological features.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
